The paper deals with a new task for fine-grained image understanding, which involves image-sentence pairs and requires semantic entailment prediction. This task is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) fields. The paper also proposes a new dataset and evaluates various VQA baselines, which involves machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
